---
description: "AI agents for every business department -- engineering, marketing, legal, finance, operations, product, sales, and support. The full Soleur agent roster."
layout: base.njk
permalink: agents/
eleventyComputed:
  title: "{{ stats.agents }} AI Agents for Solo Founders"
  seoTitle: "{{ stats.agents }} AI Agents for Solo Founders — Every Department | Soleur"
---

    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Your AI Organization: {{ stats.agents }} Specialists Across {{ stats.departments }} Departments</h1>
        <p>An AI agent is a specialist that handles a specific business function — code review, brand strategy, legal compliance, financial reporting. Soleur agents share one knowledge base, so decisions in marketing flow through to legal and operations without re-briefing. Your expertise sets direction. The agents execute.</p>
        <p><span data-last-verified="{{ site.statsLastVerified }}">{{ stats.agents }} AI agents</span> across {{ stats.departments }} business departments — from code review and architecture to marketing strategy, legal compliance, and financial reporting.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="prose">

<a href="https://x.com/karpathy/status/2019137879310836075" rel="noopener noreferrer">Agentic engineering</a> treats AI agents as specialist team members, not generic assistants. Each Soleur agent is trained for a specific business function &mdash; code review, brand strategy, legal compliance, financial reporting, competitive intelligence, and more. Together, they form a company-as-a-service organization that operates across {{ stats.departments }} departments with the depth of dedicated specialists.

What separates this from running {{ stats.departments }} disconnected tools is cross-domain coherence. Every agent shares context through a compounding knowledge base. The brand guide informs marketing copy. Competitive analysis shapes product positioning. Legal audits reference the privacy policy. A decision in one domain propagates to every other domain that depends on it.

The result: {{ stats.agents }} open source AI agents that function as a unified AI organization, not a collection of isolated capabilities. Every agent is publicly inspectable — you can review each agent's role, routing logic, and instructions in the repository. Soleur agents run on <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/overview" rel="noopener noreferrer">Claude Code</a> and the <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification" rel="noopener noreferrer">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</a>, the open standard Anthropic maintains for connecting AI models to external tools. Explore the departments below to see what each agent does.

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container">
      <nav class="category-nav" aria-label="Agent categories">
        {%- for domain in agents.domains %}
        <a href="agents/#{{ domain.key }}" class="category-pill">{{ domain.name }}</a>
        {%- endfor %}
      </nav>

      {%- for domain in agents.domains %}
      <section id="{{ domain.key }}" class="category-section">
        <div class="category-header">
          <h2 class="category-title">{{ domain.name }}</h2>
          <span class="category-count">{{ domain.count }} agent{{ "s" if domain.count != 1 }}</span>
        </div>

        {%- if domain.subcategories.length > 0 %}
          {%- for sub in domain.subcategories %}
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">{{ sub.name }}</h3>
        <div class="catalog-grid">
            {%- for agent in sub.agents %}
          <article class="component-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <span class="card-dot" style="background: {{ domain.cssVar }}"></span>
              <span class="card-category">{{ domain.name }} / {{ sub.name }}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{{ agent.name }}</h3>
            <p class="card-description">{{ agent.description }}</p>
          </article>
            {%- endfor %}
        </div>
          {%- endfor %}
        {%- else %}
        <div class="catalog-grid">
          {%- for agent in domain.agents %}
          <article class="component-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <span class="card-dot" style="background: {{ domain.cssVar }}"></span>
              <span class="card-category">{{ domain.name }}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{{ agent.name }}</h3>
            <p class="card-description">{{ agent.description }}</p>
          </article>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
        {%- endif %}
      </section>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="landing-section">
      <div class="landing-section-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What are Soleur agents?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur agents are specialized AI personas with domain expertise that execute business tasks within Claude Code. Each agent is trained for a specific function &mdash; code review, brand strategy, legal compliance, financial reporting &mdash; not a generic chatbot that attempts everything.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">How many agents does Soleur have?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur deploys {{ stats.agents }} agents across {{ stats.departments }} business departments, covering engineering, marketing, legal, finance, operations, product, sales, and support. The count updates automatically as new agents are added.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Can I customize Soleur agents?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Agents read from a shared knowledge base that includes your brand guide, project constitution, and institutional learnings. Customization happens through documentation &mdash; update your knowledge base and every agent adapts to your context automatically.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Do all Soleur agents run at once?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Agents activate only when relevant to the current task. Skills and workflows invoke the specific agents needed &mdash; a code review activates engineering reviewers, a competitive scan activates the marketing domain. Unused agents consume zero resources.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What departments do Soleur agents cover?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur provides the most comprehensive set of solo founder AI tools across {{ stats.departments }} departments: engineering, marketing, legal, finance, operations, product, sales, and support. Each department has a domain leader that orchestrates specialist agents.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

